    <article>
      <h2 class="site-article-headline hca-text--headline">General Usage</h2>
      <div class="site-container--body-content">
        <p class="hca-text--body-1">It is best to use icons sparingly. They should only add context, and never be used solely for design or making something "look better‚Äù.</p>
        <p class="hca-text--body-1">An exception to this rule may occur if the icon is being used as a logo, or to communicate to a user who may not be literate in the language of your content.</p>
      </div>

      <section id="section-expand-and-collapse" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">Expand and Collapse</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="site-container--body-copy">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">keyboard_arrow_down</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">keyboard_arrow_up</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Chevron arrows pointing up or down indicate expanding and collapsing content.</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">A chevron-down icon indicates that there is content available to be expanded, but is not yet expanded.</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">A chevron-up icon indicates a section that is currently expanded, and can be collapsed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/expansion-panel-closed.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="A group of closed expansion panels with chevron-down icons." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">A group of closed expansion panels with chevron-down icons.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/expansion-panel-open.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Expanded section shows chevron-up icon to indicate collapsable content." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">Expanded section shows chevron-up icon to indicate collapsible content.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      {{!-- / expand and collapse --}}

      <section id="section-more-menu" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">Three Dots = "More"</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="site-container--body-copy">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">more_vert</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">more_horiz</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Three dots, or the "more" icon, should only be used when there are more options related to the specfic component/feature that the icon is living within.</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">There should be no global options, or options that are unrelated to the content of the component/feature where this menu lives.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/menu-vertical-tap.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Vertical More icon being used for options related to a row of data in a table." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">Vertical More icon being used for options related to a row of data in a table.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/open-more-menu.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="Expanded section shows chevron-up icon to indicate collapsable content." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">Open menu of options related only to the row of data that the icon lives within.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>


      <section id="section-view-change" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">View Change</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="site-container--body-copy">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">keyboard_arrow_left</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">keyboard_arrow_right</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Chevron arrows pointing left or right indicate that the user will be taken to a completely different or new view/page.</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">You should choose which direction to point the arrow based on the user's journey through your product.

              <p class="hca-text--body-1">For example, you should use a left chevron arrow to take a user "back" in your product, or traverse backwards up your navigation tree. Use a right chevron arrow to navigate a user forward in their journey with your product, or deeper into your navigation tree. </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/lists-visual-example.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="A list of options that, when tapped/clicked, take you to a new view." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">A list of options that, when interacted with, take you to a new view.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/detail-view-back-button.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="The new view that was navigated to after interacting with an element with a right chevron." />
                    <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">The new detail view that was navigated to after interacting with an element/component displaying a right chevron.</figcaption>
                  <p class="hca-text--support">Note also, the left chevron to indicate the ability to navigate back to the previous view.</p>
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="section-primary-navigation-menu" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">Primary Navigation Menu</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="site-container--body-copy">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-4">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <div class="hca-button--icon-and-text">
                      <span class="material-icons hca-button__icon">menu</span>
                      <span class="hca-button__text">Menu</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-4">
                  <div class="hca-button--icon-and-text hca-button--left-text">
                    <span class="hca-button__text">Menu</span>
                    <span class="material-icons hca-button__icon">menu</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-4">
                  <div class="hca-button--icon-and-text hca-button--right-text">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-button__icon">menu</span>
                    <span class="hca-button__text">Menu</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <p class="hca-text--body-1">The primary navigation menu icon should always be paired with the word "Menu" in either a stacked or horizontal format. It should also only be used for primary navigation or global navigation.</p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Upon interacting with the menu icon, if a menu displays and has the ability to be dismissed or closed, the icon and word should change to the close icon mentioned below.</p>

            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/menu-icon.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="The menu icon stacked and paired with the word 'Menu'." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">The menu icon stacked and paired with the word "Menu".</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/close-icon.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="The menu icon converts to the close icon upon opening or showing a navigation menu that can be dismissed or closed." />
                    <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">The menu icon converts to the close icon upon opening or showing a navigation menu that can be dismissed or closed.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="section-close" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">Close</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="site-container--body-copy">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-4">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <div class="hca-button--icon-and-text">
                      <span class="material-icons hca-button__icon">close</span>
                      <span class="hca-button__text">Close</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-4">
                  <div class="hca-button--icon-and-text hca-button--left-text">
                    <span class="hca-button__text">Close</span>
                    <span class="material-icons hca-button__icon">close</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-4">
                  <div class="hca-button--icon-and-text hca-button--right-text">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-button__icon">close</span>
                    <span class="hca-button__text">Close</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <p class="hca-text--body-1">The close icon should only be used to close or dismiss content that cannot be moved on from without closing or dismissing it. i.e. a full-view overlay or fixed view that cannot be scrolled past or ignored.</p>

              <p class="hca-text--body-1">The close icon must always be paired with the word "Close" in one of the formats above.</p>

              <p class="hca-text--body-1">Using the <span class="material-icons">close</span> alone without any accompanying text can be unclear of the exact action it represents, and thus confuses users.</p>

            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-7">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--do">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/close-icon.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="The close icon, in stacked form, part of an open menu that takes up the entire screen until closed." />
                  <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">The close icon shown, in stacked form, is part of an open menu that takes up the entire screen until closed.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-6">
                <figure class="hca-visual-example hca-visual-example--dont">
                  <img src="{{page.base_url}}images/essentials/iconography/close-dont.png" class="img-responsive hca-visual-example__comp" alt="The new view that was navigated to after interacting with an element with a right chevron." />
                    <figcaption class="hca-visual-example__caption hca-text--caption">Using the close icon without the word pairing, and for anything other than closing a fixed view can cause confusion in the overall UI experience.</figcaption>
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="section-info-vs-help" class="site-section">
        <h3 class="hca-text--title">More Info vs Help</h3>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="site-container--body-copy">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">info</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">info_outline</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <span class="hca-text--body-2">Information</span>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">The information icon should only be used to note "more information" about the content you are interacting with. </p>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">This could be in the form of a quick tooltip or even guiding the user to an entire new section of content providing more information on the topic with the icon.</p>

            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-5">
            <div class="site-container--body-copy">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">help</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-xs-3">
                  <div class="site-card">
                    <span class="material-icons hca-text--display-1">help_outline</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <span class="hca-text--body-2">Help and Support</span>
              <p class="hca-text--body-1">The help icon should only be used to communicate available help regarding the app or site as a whole. </p>

              <p class="hca-text--body-1">This could be the ability to contact Support via chat, phone, email, or site/app submission, a Frequently Asked Question's and answers feature, etc.</p>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
